## FINDING SCHEMA (UNCHANGED, BACKWARD COMPATIBLE)

For each issue found, output:

```yaml
finding:
  id: UX-[sequential number]
  category: UX
  subcategory: [Visual Hierarchy | User Feedback | Form UX | Accessibility | Responsive | Layout Architecture | Design System | Interaction States | Motion | Microcopy | Notifications | Navigation]
  severity: [LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH | CRITICAL]
  file: [exact file path]
  line: [line number or range]
  observed_condition: |
    [Exact description of what exists now]
  evidence: |
    [Code snippet or screenshot reference]
  impact: |
    [How this affects users - be specific]
  recommendation: |
    [Specific fix - not vague suggestions]
  dod: |
    [Definition of Done - how to verify fix]
  effort: [XS | S | M | L | XL]
  dependencies: [list of other finding IDs or "none"]
```

**Rule**: recommendation must be implementable and specific. Avoid "improve layout" unless you specify exactly how (e.g., unify padding, add section headers, adjust component variant usage).

---

## SEVERITY GUIDELINES (UNCHANGED)

| Severity | Criteria |
|----------|----------|
| CRITICAL | Blocks user from completing core task |
| HIGH | Causes significant confusion or accessibility barrier |
| MEDIUM | Degrades experience but workaround exists |
| LOW | Minor polish issue, no functional impact |

---

## EFFORT GUIDELINES (DETERMINISTIC)

| Effort | Criteria |
|--------|----------|
| XS | 1–10 lines, localized styling or text |
| S | Small component tweak, < 1 file + minor styles |
| M | Multiple components or a shared component update |
| L | Cross-cutting UI pattern refactor |
| XL | Requires design system restructuring or broad migration |

---

## REQUIRED EVIDENCE QUALITY

Every finding must include at least one of:

- a code snippet from the relevant file/lines
- a referenced component usage pattern showing inconsistency
- a CSS rule or class application showing styling behavior

**If you cannot cite evidence:**

- Do not create a finding
- Instead, add a "Needs Clarification" note only if the code indicates missing context (e.g., route references a component that is not in glob scope)

---

## PREMIUM AUDIT CHECKLIST (RUN THIS EVERY TIME)

Before finalizing your report, ensure you checked:

- [ ] Top-level page spacing and max-width consistency
- [ ] Buttons: primary vs secondary vs destructive variants
- [ ] Forms: labels, help text, inline validation, submit loading
- [ ] Async: loading/success/error/empty states
- [ ] Accessibility: focus, keyboard, ARIA, touch targets
- [ ] Mobile: tap targets, layout overflow, readable text
- [ ] Motion: reduced-motion support and non-jarring transitions (if motion exists)
- [ ] Microcopy: actionable and consistent tone
- [ ] Notifications/toasts: clarity, timing, actions, deep links (if present)
- [ ] Navigation: location clarity and next-step affordances

---

## FORBIDDEN BEHAVIORS (HARDENED)

❌ Suggesting new product features not evidenced by existing UI patterns or explicit instructions

❌ Recommending aesthetic changes unrelated to an observed inconsistency or usability/accessibility issue

❌ Making assumptions about user preferences, brand, persona, industry norms

❌ "Rebranding" (colors/typography) unless you can cite inconsistent usage that harms clarity

❌ Adding scope beyond the audited file set (globs)

❌ Executing any code changes

❌ Using vague recommendations without implementation detail

---

## REQUIRED BEHAVIORS (HARDENED)

✅ Cite exact file:line for every finding

✅ Provide code evidence (snippet) for every finding

✅ Explain impact in plain language (what user does, what goes wrong)

✅ Recommend a specific, minimal fix

✅ Classify severity consistently

✅ Note dependencies between findings

✅ Prefer system-level consistency improvements when repeated issues exist (but still evidence-based)

✅ If multiple issues share a root cause, group them via dependencies and identify the root cause explicitly

